[The Vermont and New Mexico HPS cases are likely caused by different hantaviruses. Although the specific virus involved is not mentioned in the report above, the New York hantavirus is likely responsible for the Vermont case. Its rodent host is the white-footed mouse (_Peromyscus leucopus_).

The hantavirus responsible for the cases in New Mexico is the one mentioned in the report above, Sin Nombre. Its rodent host is the deer mouse (_P. maniculatus_). Precautions to avoid exposure to these viruses are the same for both of them.

An image of _P. leucopus_ can be accessed at http://www.fcps.edu/islandcreekes/ecology/white-footed_mouse.htm, and of _P. maniculatus_ at http://www.gpnc.org/moused.htm.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Vermont in the northeastern USA can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2784790,367 and New Mexico in the southeastern USA at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2784790,1842. - Mod.TY]
